The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for cyber security, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also extensively discusses the use of machine learning, specifically deep learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of reinforcement learning also falls under the category of machine learning, and the paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of multi-agent simulations, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
